WEBVTT

00:10:58.200 --> 00:11:00.840
one of the first psychologists
to study moral elevation.

00:11:01.360 --> 00:11:05.576
SA: Usually elevation happens in moments
when you don't really expect it,

00:11:05.600 --> 00:11:08.016
so it's these kind of surprising moments.

00:11:08.040 --> 00:11:12.136
The big picture things might be
those really exemplary things

00:11:12.160 --> 00:11:14.656
that everybody thinks about
in terms of heroes.

00:11:14.680 --> 00:11:17.936
So this person saved somebody
from a burning building.

00:11:17.960 --> 00:11:21.216
But it's the everyday stuff
that people do.

00:11:21.240 --> 00:11:24.376
AG: It's the colleague
who stays late to help out the team,

00:11:24.400 --> 00:11:27.736
the boss who shows up
to fix a broken copy machine,

00:11:27.760 --> 00:11:29.936
the client who opens up
her personal network

00:11:29.960 --> 00:11:32.096
to help you find leads for a new job.